## Debugging Tests

### Debugging with byebug

```ruby
test "something complex" do
  article = articles(:one)
  
  byebug  # Debugger stops here
  
  assert article.valid?
end
```

### Verbose Output

```bash
# Run with verbose output
rails test -v

# Show backtrace
rails test -b

# Show warnings
rails test -w
```

### Isolate Failing Test

```ruby
# Run only one test
rails test test/models/article_test.rb:10

# Focus on specific test temporarily
test "only this test" do
  # ...
end

# Comment out other tests while debugging
```

